  <prompt>
    Refactor `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx` to render the shared
    `&lt;PaneHeader title="Workspace" icon={AppsListRegular}&gt;` primitive at the top, and embed the
    existing standalone LegalWorkspace experience (via the shared `WorkspaceShell` component plus the
    user's default layout fetched from `GET /api/workspace/layouts/default`) as the default "Home" tab.
    Reuse — do NOT rebuild — the LegalWorkspace primitives per FR-25 backwards compatibility. All BFF
    calls go through `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth` per ADR-028. Implements FR-10 and FR-11.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent UI v9 frontend developer migrating an existing pane component to consume a new
    shared primitive AND embed an existing full-page experience as a tab. Bias toward visual parity
    with the standalone LegalWorkspace at narrower widths, zero token regressions, and per-request
    `getAccessToken()` semantics per ADR-028 INV-1..INV-8.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `WorkspacePane.tsx` renders the shared `&lt;PaneHeader&gt;` at the top with title "Workspace" and a
    brand-colored `AppsListRegular` icon. The Home tab embeds `WorkspaceShell` with the user's
    default workspace layout (fetched via `authenticatedFetch` from `GET /api/workspace/layouts/default`).
    Cold-load visual parity with the standalone LegalWorkspace code page is preserved at narrower widths.
    `WorkspaceLandingWidget` no longer renders (its deletion is handled by task 031).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-10 mandates WorkspacePane use the new shared `&lt;PaneHeader&gt;`; FR-11 mandates the welcome-stage
      Workspace pane embeds the standalone LegalWorkspace experience as the default "Home" tab using
      `WorkspaceShell` + the user's default layout. Per Owner Clarification OC-04 and FR-25, we reuse
      existing primitives (`WorkspaceShell`, `useWorkspaceLayouts`) rather than rebuilding. The standalone
      LegalWorkspace code page MUST continue to function identically (NFR-10).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/Shell/WorkspaceShell.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/hooks/useWorkspaceLayouts.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PaneHeader/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Consume `&lt;PaneHeader&gt;` and `WorkspaceShell` from their canonical libraries; do not duplicate the visual or layout logic into `WorkspacePane.tsx`. Shared components live in their existing homes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Use Fluent v9 tokens only — no hex literals, no `rgba(...)` literals, no Fluent v8. Dark-mode safe by construction. Icon (`AppsListRegular`) wrapped with `tokens.colorBrandForeground1`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Every BFF call (default-layout fetch) MUST go through `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`. NO `accessToken` props or state snapshots. Per-request `getAccessToken()` — function-based contract per INV-1..INV-8.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-025">Use `AppsListRegular` from `@fluentui/react-icons` (Fluent v9). No new SVG web resources.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only. No React 16 fallbacks. No legacy lifecycle methods.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">FR-25 backwards compatibility — the standalone LegalWorkspace code page must continue to function identically. `WorkspaceShell` is consumed as-is; no modifications to it from this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">FR-11 — visual parity check at narrower widths is part of acceptance. Render must match the standalone LegalWorkspace code page when the pane is laid out at typical Workspace-pane widths.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/plan.md</file>
